name: Hammer
desciption: A small, lightweight tool used in the building industry. Can also be used as a weapon.

name: Baseball Bat
desciption: A long, solid wooden bat. As a weapon, it can land quite a blow on your enemy.

name: Crowbar
desciption: Used for opening crates and large boxes. The sharp hook at one end makes this a great weapon.

name: Knuckle Dusters
desciption: They won't know what hit them with these strong, hard, brass knuckle dusters. They won't even see it coming!

name: Pen Knife
desciption: High quality knife--a great survival tool. Ideal for climbers, adventurers, military personnel, and close combat in dark alleys.

name: Kitchen Knife
desciption: Do your attempts to prepare food like your favourite TV chef end up more like hack and saw than slice and dice? If so, a sharp new knife could be your saviour.

name: Dagger
desciption: A short, sharp metal dagger useful for quick attacks. Straight in, straight out.

name: Axe
desciption: Used mainly for chopping tree roots and splitting kindling. Can bash and split many other substances, too.

name: Scimitar
desciption: The deeply-curved, high-carbon steel blade of the scimitar can terrify your opponent as you attack with a swashbuckling slash.

name: Chainsaw
desciption: A compact chainsaw lets you cut quickly in tight spots. Its standard diamond chain is more than a match for almost anything you might need to slice up.

name: Samurai Sword
desciption: A ninja-grade, full-tang samurai sword, created for us by a master artisan. The sword balances perfectly, takes and holds a razor edge, and can divide an eyelash or a full skull in one swipe.

name: Glock 17
desciption: The Glock 17 is a lightweight semi-automatic pistol holding up to 20 rounds in a magazine.

name: Raven MP25
desciption: The Raven MP25 holds 6 rounds per magazine. It can deliver powerful, quick blows to the opponent at short range.

name: Ruger 57
desciption: A fast firing pistol chambered for the 5.7mm cartridge, holding 20 rounds per magazine. An accurate and moderately powerful weapon.

name: Beretta M9
desciption: The M9 Beretta is the standard Army sidearm. Accurate and fast firing. 17 rounds per magazine.

name: USP
desciption: A good short range weapon that holds 15 rounds per magazine. Very accurate and has fast semi-automatic firing.

name: Beretta 92FS
desciption: A direct-feed, double-stacked pistol with a 20-round magazine. This model has improvements to prevent the slide flying off if it cracks.

name: Fiveseven
desciption: A small and light firearm that holds up to 20 rounds per magazine. Widely used by counter-terrorists all around the world.

name: Magnum
desciption: A very slow but powerful weapon. It holds only 6 rounds, but delivers a mighty blow to the enemy.

name: Desert Eagle
desciption: Fast-firing and very powerful. If you hit your opponent, he goes down and stays down. The magazine only holds eight rounds but the strength of each impact makes up for that.

name: Dual 92G Berettas
desciption: One of the greatest pistols in the world. And when you are packing a pair, the results are incredible: 46 powerful shots to take your opponent down. The Dual 92G Berettas are very hard to get hold of, so cost a premium. But the extra impact is worth the extra price.

name: Sawed-Off Shotgun
desciption: Loads and fires two cartridges at a time. If you hit your opponent, you will open up a huge hole.

name: Benelli M1 Tactical
desciption: Simple and sturdy. Takes seven cartridges and delivers each round with power.

name: MP5 Navy
desciption: Lightweight and air-cooled, one of the most widely used submachine guns in the world. 30 rounds per magazine.

name: P90
desciption: Effective close-range automatic weapon. 50-round magazine. Not particularly accurate, but its fast firing will cause heavy damage on anything it hits.

name: AK-47
desciption: Powerful, accurate and virtually unbreakable. This 30-round magazine fed rifle is a favourite among discerning hit men.

name: M4A1 Colt Carbine
desciption: The Colt is a powerful and accurate rifle. It's one of the best weapons around, a good choice!

name: Benelli M4 Super
desciption: The Auto Shotgun is the best close-range weapon around. Although you may have to reload often as it only holds 7 rounds, the amount of rounds you can pump into your enemy in just a few seconds is amazing.

name: M16 A2 Rifle
desciption: Much like the Colt, but more powerful and accurate. 30 rounds per magazine, with a fast-fire option.

name: Steyr AUG
desciption: The Steyr AUG holds 30 rounds. It can be very accurate, although its standard scope is a little weak. A great weapon for the price.

name: M249 SAW
desciption: The M249 Squad Automatic Weapon is a light machine-gun that combines the precision and mobility of a rifle with the relentless ferocity of rapid machine-gun fire. A favorite of the US Military, this gas-operated LMG can cut down several targets in a matter of seconds.

name: Leather Vest
desciption: Simple and lightweight. If you're lucky, it will protect you from a few shots.

name: Police Vest
desciption: Strong and durable body armor that will absorb a lot of damage to your torso.

name: Bulletproof Vest
desciption: Body armor that can absorb a certain amount of heavy-weapons fire, although it will not turn you into Iron Man.

name: Box of Chocolate Bars
desciption: A box of chocolate bars. Provides a small happiness increase when consumed.

name: Big Box of Chocolate Bars
desciption: A very large box of chocolate bars. Provides a small happiness increase when consumed.

name: Bag of Bon Bons
desciption: A pack of Bon Bons. Provides a small happiness increase when consumed.

name: Box of Bon Bons
desciption: A box of four luxurious Bon Bons. Provides a small happiness increase when consumed.

name: Box of Extra Strong Mints
desciption: Wow, whoever needs these must have very bad breath. Provides a small happiness increase when consumed.

name: Pack of Music CDs
desciption: Some of the hottest bands around, all in one pack of CDs.

name: DVD Player
desciption: Sony DVD player with MP3 reading ability.

name: MP3 Player
desciption: Brand new MP3 player made by Sony. Comes with a 512 MEG card.

name: CD Player
desciption: This stylish home stereo system was top of the range back in 1994, with its CD player capable of reading even the most scratched up compact discs in your collection.

name: Blank DVDs : 100
desciption: This spindle pack of 100 writable DVD-R DVDs are suitable for video and data applications, and compatible with a variety of different drives.

name: Hard Drive
desciption: A large hard drive to extend your computer's storage capacity.

name: Tank Top
desciption: A stylish low cut tank top.

name: Trainers
desciption: A nice pair of trainers.

name: Jacket
desciption: A very stylish summer jacket.

name: Full Body Armor
desciption: Full body armor made of high-grade bulletproof material. It will absorb some of the damage from hits taken by the wearer.

name: Outer Tactical Vest
desciption: Despite the Combat Vest offering improved protection, its predecessor the Outer Tactical Vest is far from obsolete. The increased survivability and enhanced maneuverability provided makes it a more than worthwhile addition to your combat wardrobe.

name: Plain Silver Ring
desciption: A simple silver ring.

name: Sapphire Ring
desciption: A sapphire ring.

name: Gold Ring
desciption: A solid gold ring.

name: Diamond Ring
desciption: An expensive diamond ring.

name: Pearl Necklace
desciption: Matched cultured pearls in an understated but elegant setting.

name: Silver Necklace
desciption: A silver necklace featuring a pattern of semi-precious stones.

name: Gold Necklace
desciption: A mesmerizing spiral of 14-karat gold.

name: Plastic Watch
desciption: This watch is absolutely accurate at least twice a day.

name: Stainless Steel Watch
desciption: Continues working when dropped, stepped on, or hit with a rubber mallet.

name: Gold Watch
desciption: Elegance and luxury at sixty seconds per minute.

name: Personal Computer
desciption: A high-tech personal computer. Can be used to program viruses.

name: Microwave
desciption: A brand new microwave.

name: Minigun
desciption: This gun has a 200-round magazine. When you are done with a burst, your enemy will be in fragments.

name: Pack of Cuban Cigars
desciption: A pack of great quality, very expensive Cuban cigars.

name: Television
desciption: A king size Sony TV screen.

name: Morphine
desciption: Known on the street as Miss Emma, Morphine is a potent opiate painkiller whose addictive qualities are less than ladylike. With one shot, you'll be taken on a high-speed trip to your happy place, a pleasant destination where your leg is in one piece and your face is no longer mangled beyond repair.

name: First Aid Kit
desciption: This comprehensive collection of medical necessities contains everything you need to treat burns, blood loss, and broken bones. Whether you're bleeding out on the battlefield or you've slipped in the bath and sat on a shampoo bottle, you'll be back on your feet in moments.

name: Small First Aid Kit
desciption: A small medical kit containing bandages, gauze, and antiseptic wipes. There's not enough in here to put someone's guts back in, but you'll have no problem patching up a minor flesh-wound or a nasty boo-boo on your knee.

name: Simple Virus
desciption: A very simple virus that was written by an amateur.

name: Polymorphic Virus
desciption: Polymorphic viruses are semi-sentient: they adapt themselves with each infection. With a virus-writing toolkit you can even design new viruses.

name: Tunneling Virus
desciption: This virus will attempt to tunnel under anti-virus monitoring programs in order to bypass their monitoring functions.

name: Armored Virus
desciption: This virus attempts to make disassembly difficult. Great for systems with weak virus protection.

name: Stealth Virus
desciption: In order to avoid detection, a virus will often take over virus protection system functions likely to spot it and use them to hide itself. An extremely hard virus to write.

name: Santa Hat '04
desciption: A well crafted Santa hat made especially for the 2004 Christmas!

name: Christmas Cracker '04
desciption: An expensive Christmas cracker made especially for the 2004 Christmas!

name: Snow Cannon
desciption: A very rare special weapon, made and crafted by Santa himself!

name: Tabata RM2
desciption: Considered a must-have for those in Class D, the Japanese-made Tabata RM2 possesses a stunning amount of top-end speed - just make sure you leave yourself plenty of time to stop! This vehicle is a great Class D option on long tarmac tracks.

name: Edomondo NSX
desciption: Edomondo's NSX is often at the top of most drivers' list when they reach Class A, and is a must-have for those who consider themselves an elite racer. If you're looking to set records on a track that will test your car's handling and braking, the NSX has no equal, with this model finding its home on some of Torn's most testing tracks.

name: Echo Quadrato
desciption: Echo' Quadrato is a popular among both the ladies and the lads, as its streamlined exterior means it has no problem getting up to speed from a cold start. Sadly, European road laws mean this vehicle is limited when it comes to speed, hence why it tops out at a measly 155mph.

name: Bavaria M5
desciption: Class B racers whose budget can't stretch to a Colina Tanprice could do much worse than a Bavaria M5. The fastest 4-door saloon of its type, the M5 model has a top speed of 186mph, but it will take some time to get there due to its subpar acceleration ability.

name: Bavaria Z8
desciption: The Bavaria Z8's rear wheel drive means it can often struggle for grip off the line, so if you're heading to a drag race you'll probably want something a little more reactive. But if you're taking this Class C car down a few windy roads, the Z8's poise and balance make this car stable under braking, giving you a crucial speed advantage on corners.

name: Chevalier CZ06
desciption: Like most American cars, Chevalier's CZ06 doesn't handle particularly well. But what it lacks in maneuverability it more than makes up for with a sky-high top speed thanks to its glorious 7 liter V8 engine. The CZ06 is one of the most popular options for Class C drivers as it is the fastest in its class.

name: Dart Rampager
desciption: An all-American icon, the Dart Rampager is as fast as it is chaotic, with this vehicle treating corners as a suggestion rather than a guide. You'll likely abandon the Dart once you've finished your time in Class B, but you can be sure that your ride to the top is an absolute gas.

name: Knight Firebrand
desciption: Weak cornering caused by severe understeer means that the Knight Firebrand relies heavily on its straight line speed in order to remain competitive. In that respect, the Firebrand can tussle with the best cars Class C has to offer - just don't expect it to do well in a small, country village.

name: Volt GT
desciption: Volt's GT model handles like a racing car should, but is slightly let down by its acceleration, despite its low weight. Nevertheless, this model is often unbeatable down at the Docks, and comes recommended as a versatile option for drivers who are new to Class A racing.

name: Invader H3
desciption: This civilian version of a military favorite works fantastically on the dirt thanks to its superb braking ability, making it a fine, albeit slower Class D alternative to the Bavaria X5. You won't want to take this beast on the freeway, however, as not only is it highly unsuited to tarmac, you'll also look like a massive wally driving this through the city.

name: Echo S4
desciption: The Echo S4's superb braking ability allows it to really dig in on the corners, making for a great exit speed once the turbos kick in. The S4 won't win any awards for acceleration due to its limiting four wheel drive system, but it remains a staple in the garage of many great Class B drivers.

name: Edomondo IR
desciption: The IR model is slow for its class and suffers from braking issues, but the superior handling for which Edomondo is known makes this a decent option for those battling away in Class C. Widely regarded as one of the best front-wheel drive cars of all time, the IR is the closest you'll get to a race car from a factory model.

name: Edomondo ACD
desciption: Edomondos are often blessed with great handling, and the ACD is no exception thanks to its wide wheelbase and stiff suspension springs. The car's weight is its biggest downfall, however, and this drags back the ACD's top speed to make it a mid-range option among Class D cars.

name: Edomondo Localé
desciption: The Edomondo Localé is popular among those new to racing due to its recommendation in Baldr's racing guide. In fact, so versatile is the Localé, that some drivers have been known to take it all the way from Class E to A, a strategy that allows them to save those precious racing points for future use.

name: Verpestung Insecta
desciption: Described as one of the few good things to come out of WWII, the Verpestung Insecta's limited top speed may put some consumers off this cheap and cheerful vehicle. But for Class D racers, the Insecta is a versatile motor whose handling allows it to compete with faster cars on short tarmac tracks full of sharp turns.

name: Chevalier CVR
desciption: Like most American cars, the Chevalier CVR simply cannot take a corner, so you're limited as to what you can achieve with this vehicle. What you do get is a beast of an engine at 2,800cc, so don't be surprised if you see the CVR zipping past you midway through a Class D race, only to let you pass with ease on the inside.

name: Volt MNG
desciption: Volt's MNG is an iconic car for one reason and one reason alone - it is literally unstoppable. Its combination of an extreme top speed and brakes made of sponge means you're just as likely to see the back of an ambulance as you are the chequered flag when driving this thing. Baldr's guide considers the MNG to be one of the best Class B cars around, but those in the Torn City hospital refer to their drivers as organ donors.

name: Trident
desciption: As you might expect from a three wheeler, the Trident isn't much in terms of pace, and is actually one of the slowest cars available in Torn City. That being said, this iconic car's handling isn't too bad for an E class vehicle - just don't go heavy on the brakes into a sharp turn, or you may topple over!

name: Oceania SS
desciption: Pacy but poor out of the blocks is an apt description of the Oceania SS - but hey, it works for Usain Bolt! This Australian powerhouse comes recommended for class C tarmac races, but if you're approaching a corner you'd be advised to check your rear-view mirror, because nine times out of ten there will be someone on your shoulder.

name: Coat Hanger
desciption: A metal coat hanger, often used for picking the locks of cars.

name: Bunch of Flowers
desciption: A bunch of flowers, a perfect gift!

name: Neutrilux 2000
desciption: Very rare: a Leprechaun's most powerful weapon, created out of green nuclear energy. Or at least, that's how the legend goes.

name: Springfield 1911
desciption: Steel and light weight aluminium frames, stainless, blued and parkerized finishes, V-12 barrel porting... What more could you want?

name: Egg Propelled Launcher
desciption: Very rare: the Easter Bunny's most powerful weapon, created out of jelly bean and chocolate egg technology.

name: Bunny Suit
desciption: Very rare, and created out of the strongest fur yet discovered, this serves as the Easter Bunny's most stylish and most protective armor.

name: Chocolate Egg '05
desciption: Every person's favourite treat, made for the 2005 Easter celebration!

name: Firewalk Virus
desciption: This type of virus is unknown.

name: Game Console
desciption: This Game Console is a generic gaming device exclusive to Torn City, and was made from parts cannibalized from an Xbox, PlayStation, and a Sega Saturn. Game Consoles are unique in that they actually bring people happiness when they put effort into them, unlike careers, relationships, or children.

name: Xbox
desciption: A games console used for playing games.

name: Parachute
desciption: A collapsible device used to retard the descent of a falling body.

name: Trench Coat
desciption: A thick trench coat that covers most of the body.

name: 9mm Uzi
desciption: This Uzi is a compact, boxy, light-weight sub machine gun used throughout the world as a police and special forces firearm.

name: RPG Launcher
desciption: The anti-tank RPG launcher is one of the most common and most effective infantry weapons in contemporary conflicts.

name: Leather Bullwhip
desciption: A whip made of rawhide. In the right hands, it can be a stealthy and deadly weapon. In the wrong hands...you may lose an eye!

name: Ninja Claws
desciption: Traditional ninja weapon for close combat, with four needle-sharp spikes.

name: Test Trophy
desciption: Test!

name: Pet Rock
desciption: One of the rarest items in Torn, first discovered by Matt. Warning: this pet is extremely dangerous! Only the very brave or the very stupid should take it on. Matt takes no responsibility for the loss of life or fingertips caused by this pet.

name: Non-Anon Doll
desciption: The perfect gift for when you want to add insult to injury. Patented by Someone...

name: Poker Doll
desciption: Feisty red haired doll made in the image of Peachy complete with bellybutton poking action!

name: Yoda Figurine
desciption: Have a doll like Yoda You must.

name: Trojan Horse
desciption: This sweet gift from Tebbs seems innocently useful. Inside, it is highly infectious!

name: Doll's Head
desciption: A doll's head owned by the Evil Female Admin known as Wynn. Believed to be responsible for lost stats, site lag, mass kicks on IRC, and random deletions.

name: Rubber Ducky of Doom
desciption: Most powerful weapon in the game can only be used by those with the knowledge to unleash its fearsome Duck Powers. Most often used after being asked the same n00b question for the 5th time in a row. Has also been seen dive bombing random people in IRC.

name: Teppic Bear
desciption: Only known of by a very select few, this Teddy Bear stands as proof that even the toughest of players, such as Teppic, do indeed have a softer side.

name: RockerHead Doll
desciption: It has no uses and does nothing just like the staff member it resembles.

name: Mouser Doll
desciption: Similar to the one used by Mouser to relieve the stress of dealing with uncooperative staff, annoying n00bs, and day to day business of being a Coder in Torn City.

name: Elite Action Man
desciption: Mimics the actions of the real man. Has been known to abuse Caps Lock Abusers.

name: Toy Reactor
desciption: Miniature model of a Nuclear Reactor similar to the one that Sec. Les_Claypool will be working on when he leaves for the Navy.

name: Royal Doll
desciption: This doll will give its user the feeling of being royalty just like KingAce while in possession. Player will receive special treatment from friends and rivals while carrying this special item!

name: Blue Dragon
desciption: A blue dragon spawned from the evil TC admin named blue comes packed with evil intentions and wild powers.. Some say rubbing the dragons head makes one 100 times stronger than any normal man!

name: China Tea Set
desciption: Be just like Chedburn, sit in the garden and sip tea with this China Tea Set.

name: Mufasa Toy
desciption: Replica of a plush toy owned by Randi it looks just like the majestic lion Mufasa... before he was trampled of course.

name: Dozen Roses
desciption: A dozen roses. This bouquet is available in assorted colors, from red for that special someone to black to send to your enemy after you hospitalize him or her.

name: Skanky Doll
desciption: Just like the one owned by Infrit, this doll comes with blood red lipstick, a mini skirt, and a corset.

name: Lego Hurin
desciption: This life like model is comprised completely of legos. Comes with upgrades such as the multi hunting goggles and evilarium connects to the brain. Read instructions for more details. Not intended for use by children age 6 and under.

name: Mystical Sphere
desciption: A rare object created by Phyrax when he was a helper... Only possessed by a select few in all of Torn City. Every now and then lights and mist shoot out of the sphere and at this time the holder may obtain all knowledge and wisdom.

name: 10 Ton Pacifier
desciption: Used for that special baby out there.. the one you would like to crush because you just cant get them to stop crying. Drive this pacifier in their mouth and you will get dead silence. Created by Rock for all the babies out there.

name: Horse Toy
desciption: First seen by those who crossed the Godfather, this strange object greatly increases your desire to annoy people in the chat rooms, while simultaneously draining away all your religious beliefs.

name: Uriel's Speakers
desciption: These tripped out speakers will blow you away with thundering bass and a beat that won't quit. Putting out 5000W with a crushing 600 decibels.

name: Strife Clown
desciption: This Ominous Clown is full of discord. This rare item channels all the pain and torture this world has to offer.

name: Locked Teddy
desciption: This bear is covered in chains connected with padlocks. He has been seen locking forum topics around Torn City, but has yet to have any of his locks picked.

name: Riddle's Bat
desciption: This baseball bat belongs to Riddle. All know it and most fear it. It causes panic in the IRC realm. Random kicks occur when he is in a bad mood or when mass slapping occurs. Don't mess with the bat!

name: Soup Nazi Doll
desciption: Often seen running loose on IRC, usually before kicking rule breakers with the message No Soup For You!! Believed to have been released by Lestat.

name: Pouncer Doll
desciption: Be careful of Pouncer. She might pounce on you unexpectedly, or hit you with a pillow or ducks, just like her creator SexySassy.

name: Spammer Doll
desciption: A very friendly doll with good interactions, until you make it mad. It can hit back pretty hard, and it will start spamming you, even when you think it should be sleeping, just like Templar.

name: Cookie Jar
desciption: Cookie Jar - Just like the one Is0lati0n has at home, this jar is stocked full of chocolate cookies for late nights working in the IRC channel.

name: Vanity Mirror
desciption: Complete with 24 carat gold rim and handle with YT's initials engraved on it.

name: Banana Phone
desciption: Bright yellow, shaped like a banana, and plays Titan's favourite song when it rings. Known to annoy other staff members... may be part of the reason he loves it.

name: Xbox 360
desciption: A games console used for playing games.

name: Yasukuni Sword
desciption: A rare Japanese blade of exceptional quality and craftsmanship.

name: Rusty Sword
desciption: An old rusty sword.

name: Dance Toy
desciption: Although its name refers to Syrup it's nothing near slow. Just press the button on the back and watch this crazy toy dance himself to death!

name: Lucky Dime
desciption: Found deep within a lost cavern in Torn City was a rare bag of dimes that were stolen during the first bank robbery in Torn City. They were thought to have been lost forever, but a few have survived and are said to bring luck to those who play roulette in the Casino.

name: Crystal Carousel
desciption: Created by w1ld_h0rs3s this replica Carousel shows her favourite horses running wild and free.

name: Pixie Sticks
desciption: Small plastic tubes filled with flavoured sugar. Available in orange, raspberry, grape and strawberry. Provides a large happiness increase when consumed.

name: Ice Sculpture
desciption: Some believe that the reclusive artist who carved these sculptures meant them to depict friendliness and good will. However, some who gaze on these rare pieces feel an icy coldness and a sinking detachment from the world. Only the artist knows his true intent.

name: Case of Whiskey
desciption: Recovered during a raid at his Mansion this is the last case of Whiskey that mdshare produced before being captured by Torn City Police for violation of the alcohol ordinance.

name: Laptop
desciption: A high-tech wireless laptop. You can use it on your long travels to check your mail and see how things are going at home.

name: Purple Frog
desciption: A very rare species of frog that lives in Torn City. Sometimes seen on IRC hopping into people's pockets. Usually friendly, but can become extremely violent if provoked.

name: Hooorang's Key
desciption: Hooorang's skeleton key lets you bypass any locked doors and open lockers and safes. Nothing can stop its holder. Holding this item makes you feel invincible.

name: Patriot Whip
desciption: UTBracket's own design, comes in either Union Jack or St. George style. Don't mess with the owner of this collectible or expect to have your day ruined by some painful marks on your butt and the ability to sit down removed!!

name: Statue Of Aeolus
desciption: Aeolus Keeper of The Wind possess the power to control the strength and direction of the wind. A Greek Mystical Artifact with powers believed to be related to the wind.

name: Bolt Cutters
desciption: A pair of quality bolt cutters. Made of tempered steel with cushion-grip handles and durable, heat-treated jaws.

name: Photographs
desciption: Four photographs of a man handing over a briefcase.

name: Black Unicorn
desciption: A friend for life and a ferocious fighter feared by all foes.

name: WarPaint Kit
desciption: The perfect accessory when going off to war. Fashioned after Scarlet's own personal kit, containing facial paints made of wolf's blood. Once applied, the user is said to gain the prowess of the wolf.

name: Official Ninja Kit
desciption: The Official Hiro Ninja Kit is a custom fit accessory set for any wannabe ninja. Contains: ninja suit for those stealthy attacks, grappling hook for those difficult larcenies, ninja guide book as penned by Hiro himself. Warning - not for novices.

name: Leukaemia Teddy Bear
desciption: Soft and fluffy, it likes to be cuddled and can comfort you on those lonely nights. But beware: mistreatment of your Leukaemia Teddy Bear will result in a mighty slap from its paws of steel.

name: Chocobo Flute
desciption: Long thought to be lost forever this small item was found in the far reaches of Torn City by CloudFFVII. Many believe peace of mind and swiftness in battle are brought to the holder of this charm.

name: Annoying Man
desciption: This little annoying man can be seen on IRC and on MSN annoying people and getting into trouble just like Manjot.

name: Article on Crime
desciption: An article written by the reporter George on specific criminals.

name: Unknown
desciption: This item does not exist.

name: Barbie Doll
desciption: Equipped with Kung Fu Grip, and hot pink nail polish, this doll resembles the Admin Clansdancer.

name: Wand of Destruction
desciption: A very rare special weapon, this wand was created by The Great Pumpkin himself to wreak havoc on Torn City.

name: Jack-O-Lantern '05
desciption: Given out by The Great Pumpkin, to good boys and girls all across Torn City.

name: Gasoline
desciption: Capable of storing five gallons of pure liquid warehouse repellent, this rusty red can makes it easy to transport gasoline across the city to your destination of choice. If you're an arsonist, that destination could be a church, a brothel, or something weird like a yurt. If you're Toxic Terry, that gas is going on a straight shot to your digestive tract.

name: Butterfly Knife
desciption: A small knife, deadly in the right hands. The handles fold up to conceal the blade of this dangerous weapon.

name: XM8 Rifle
desciption: Lightweight assault rifle, deadly when fired up close. Can break through the toughest armor.

name: Taser
desciption: An electroshock gun, non lethal, but will land your opponent in the hospital for a while just as quickly as a more aggressive weapon will.

name: Chain Mail
desciption: Chain Mail consists of a series of individual metal rings linked together to form a mesh, resulting in a flexible yet resilient barrier capable of protecting the wearer during hand-to-hand combat. This form of armor was most commonly used by European warriors between 300 BC - 1600 AD, but today is mostly worn by overweight war reenactors who like to play dress-up on the weekends.

name: Cobra Derringer
desciption: A small, lightweight pistol. For some people two bullets are all you need.

name: Flak Jacket
desciption: Marine issued armor. Sturdy and effective against most small caliber rounds.

name: Birthday Cake '05
desciption: A slice of cake left over from Torn's first birthday.

name: Bottle of Beer
desciption: Immortalised by the Reel Big Fish song of the same name, Beer is the most popular alcoholic drink in the world, beating fancy-pants wine into second place. The earliest evidence for the brewing of beer dates back 13,000 years, though given mankind's vigorous consumption of the beverage, it could be much older and we've just forgotten.

name: Bottle of Champagne
desciption: A sparkling wine associated with royalty, celebration, and the launching of ships, Champagne may only be legally named as such if it originates from the Champagne wine region of France. However, this law only applies in parts of the world with nothing better to care about, hence why there are no repercussions for pretending that this generic bottle of fizzy plonk contains genuine champers.

name: Soap on a Rope
desciption: Necessity for the often-jailed felon.

name: Single Red Rose
desciption: For when words alone just aren't enough to say how you feel.

name: Bunch of Black Roses
desciption: Not sure your opponent got the meaning of that 4 hour hospital stay? Make SURE you get your point across with this bouquet of black roses.

name: Bunch of Balloons '05
desciption: Large bunch of brightly coloured balloons left over from the First Birthday of Torn City. How they stay inflated after the party's over, no one will ever figure out.

name: Sheep Plushie
desciption: Baaaaaa.

name: Teddy Bear Plushie
desciption: Soft plush teddy bear for your special someone to cuddle up with when you're not around.

name: Cracked Crystal Ball
desciption: A small glass globe with several deep cracks running through it. How can this be of any use?

name: S&W Revolver
desciption: Smith and Wesson revolver, commonly used in the game of Russian Roulette.

name: C4 Explosive
desciption: A C4 high-explosive device.

name: Memory Locket
desciption: It has a picture of a happy family inside it.

name: Rainbow Stud Earring
desciption: This earring is a symbol of Pride and Love.

name: Hamster Toy
desciption: Small plush hamster in a plastic ball. Replica of the one that powers parts of the TC Database and cause for most of the lag when he takes a weekend off. Known to annoy kittens and ducks alike he seems to like only one rather isolated admin.

name: Snowflake '05
desciption: A small crystal snowflake made especially for the 2005 Xmas season.

name: Christmas Tree '05
desciption: A fully decorated Christmas tree, perfect for decorating your home for the 2005 Christmas season.

name: Cannabis
desciption: This ain't your garden variety bud, no sir. Torn's Cannabis is so strong it'll melt the anxiety from your bones and dribble it out your ass. After a couple of puffs, you'll feel a special kind of relaxed that rids you of all fear, rendering you capable of some seriously heinous acts. Burgle a home? Why not. Pickpocket an old lady? Sounds fun! Dismember and dispose of a corpse you say? That's just a walk in the park, quite literally.

name: Ecstasy
desciption: Hello, boys and girls. This is your old pal stinky wizzleteats. This is a song about a whale. No, this is a song about being happy. That's right, it's the happy, happy, joy, joy, song. Happy, happy, joy, joy. Happy, happy, joy, joy. Happy, happy, joy, joy. Happy, happy, joy, joy. Happy, happy, joy, joy. Happy, happy, joy, joy. Happy, happy, joy, joy, joy.

name: Ketamine
desciption: Originally deployed as a surgical anaesthetic during the Vietnam War, Ketamine is also popular among recreational drug users due to its capacity to induce dissociative sensations and hallucinations. However, in Torn City, you'll find its users in the foxhole rather than a k-hole, with ket used to numb the body against incoming attacks. Because everyone knows that if you can't feel it, it didn't happen!

name: LSD
desciption: Wanna get mad stupid? Drop a tab of acid and let fate control your body as your mind takes a trip to dreamland. While your consciousness is pre-occupied with the effects of this potent psychedelic, your physical form will be hit by a maelstrom of effects, rendering you strong yet slow, braced and bumbling. And once the surge of pleasure and enthusiasm has washed away, you may find yourself standing over what's left of your opponent's pulped human face.

name: Opium
desciption: Prescribed for a range of ailments from diarrhea and psychosis through to menstrual pain and bronchitis, Opium is a reliable reliever of pain, consequence, and reality. Fortified by this timeless drug, your opponent's blows will feel naught more than tiny mouse breaths upon your body. And should you still find yourself laid up in the hospital, this medical marvel will see you right as rain in no time.

name: PCP
desciption: If you've ever been beaten to a pulp by a wide-eyed, grinning maniac, chances are they were hepped up on angel dust. PCP can turn even the most serene wallflower into a psychotic force of nature, imbibing users with the strength of an ox and the dexterity of an ox's effeminate young cousin who left his mining town to join the ballet. Essentially, this drug gives you all the physical benefits of being severely mentally challenged but without the obvious downsides.

name: Mr Torn Crown '07
desciption: Awarded to GZUS [18690] for winning the Mr Torn City awards 2007!

name: Shrooms
desciption: Have you ever found a blank sheet of paper absolutely fascinating? You soon will with a little help from a dose of Shrooms. These fantasy-inducing fungi tap into the brain's serotonin receptors to flood your gray matter with happy chemicals, transforming the mundane into magical in mere moments. Many people report feeling a little tired after taking psilocybin mushrooms, but don't worry, because the tap-dancing gorilla at the end of your bed will cuddle you to sleep.

name: Speed
desciption: Speed does exactly what it says on the tin, making your hands move so fast your opponent will think they're having a stroke. But don't get too cocky, because while you're busy trying to land a hit, your clouded mind leaves you open to a counterattack. Sacrificing dexterity for velocity, you'll be equal parts swift and vulnerable, like a premature baby on rocket skates.

name: Vicodin
desciption: Vicodin is a powerful pain medication which is frequently abused by those looking to gain an edge in battle. The drug's ability to inhibit the body's pain perception allows users to perform physical feats at a higher level than before, while also making them a wee bit giddy. However, while Vicodin's effect on your strength, speed, defense, and dexterity is temporary, its damage to your liver is anything but.

name: Xanax
desciption: Xanax in Torn City is very different to your typical pharmacy-bought Alprazolam, with its sedative effects giving way to an explosion of relentless energy. Researchers speculate that this phenomenon is rooted in the drug's ability to boost adenosine triphosphate production within neural cells, supercharging the brain into an overclocked state capable of firing neurons like a machine-gun. However it works, Torn Xanax is the grease that oils the gears of war, elevating a soldier to a state of aggressive frenzy that would make a Nazi Stormtrooper look like a slowpoke sissy.

name: Ms Torn Crown '07
desciption: Awarded to Vixen_ [140202] for winning the Miss Torn City awards 2007!

name: Unknown
desciption: This item does not exist.

name: Box of Sweet Hearts
desciption: Fun filled heart shaped candies with messages for your loved ones. Provides a small happiness increase when consumed.

name: Bag of Chocolate Kisses
desciption: Sweet candy kiss for the one you love. Provides a small happiness increase when consumed.

name: Crazy Cow
desciption: This is the most Famous Cow of Torn City protector of innocent pets, punisher of the scammer but watch out! Get to close to him and BOOM You have Mad Cow Disease.

name: Legend's Urn
desciption: This item is a urn holding all of the ashes of fallen legends killed by the Legend Killer himself.

name: Dreamcatcher
desciption: DL's dream catcher. Hung above a bed or in a window, catches bad dreams while good dreams slip on by.

name: Brutus Keychain
desciption: This key chain stands as proof the bearer has survived a brush with the mammoth known as Brutus.

name: Kitten Plushie
desciption: A small plush kitten. Rumour has it, if you pet its nose it will purr, but is more often heard saying Rawr!

name: Single White Rose
desciption: Found only near Valentine's Day in Torn City, this rose would be the perfect gift for your loved one on that special day.

name: Claymore Sword
desciption: The claymore is the mother of all broadswords. It's a huge, two-handed thing, approx 4ft long. Do you have the strength to wield this monster?

name: Crossbow
desciption: A crossbow has more impact damage than a normal bow and is capable of easily piercing metal.

name: Enfield SA-80
desciption: Gas-powered Enfield SA80 rifles have been the weapon of choice for the British Armed Forces since the 1980's. This edition comes with iron sights as standard, but various telescopic sights can be added to increase its aiming accuracy.

name: Grenade
desciption: A small fragmentation grenade. Pull the pin, count to three, then throw it at your enemy.

name: Stick Grenade
desciption: Stick grenades are less powerful and have shorter fuses than their British counterparts, but weigh significantly less.

name: Flash Grenade
desciption: Often used to blind opponents, can give an edge in battle that is very hard to overcome.

name: Jackhammer
desciption: A gas operated, fully automatic only shotgun. Able to fire 240 rounds per minute, this is not your average shotgun.

name: Swiss Army Knife
desciption: Elegant and light weight pocket knife, with several useful tools integrated.

name: Mag 7
desciption: Shotgun intended specially for close combat and operations in confined spaces, like the room-to-room searches.

name: Smoke Grenade
desciption: Typically used to send signals or create a smokescreen, this grenade can be used to temporarily blind your opponent, to allow you the upper hand in attacking.

name: Spear
desciption: A spear is an ancient weapon used for hunting and war, consisting of a shaft, usually of wood, with a sharpened head.

name: Vektor CR-21
desciption: Its futuristic looks are the result of the fact that the entire stock is made of a high-impact polymer. The only metal to be seen on the outside is part of the barrel and the flash-suppressor.

name: Claymore Mine
desciption: The mine contains 700 steel spheres (10.5 grains) and 1-1/2 pound layer of composition C-4 explosive and is initiated by an electric blasting cap.

name: Flare Gun
desciption: Can work as a weapon in a pinch, but only as a last resort. Works best as a device to create light in some of the darker missions.

name: Heckler & Koch SL8
desciption: H&K SL8 is a lightweight semi automatic gas powered rifle. With a unique stock design this dependable weapon is widely sought after.

name: SIG 550
desciption: The SIG 550 is a custom assault rifle. With a 20 round magazine this weapon can switch between semi automatic and full automatic firing with a flip of a switch.

name: BT MP9
desciption: Offers a lower and more controllable rate of fire compared to other handguns, is also small enough to be effectively fired with one hand.

name: Chain Whip
desciption: Oriental version of the flail. Consists of 4 to 6 iron bars linked end to end by short lengths of chain.

name: Wooden Nunchaku
desciption: Consists of two wooden bars linked by a short length of chain.

name: Kama
desciption: A simple but very sharp and potentially deadly weapon like a small sickle, a favourite of ninjas.

name: Kodachi
desciption: This 2-foot blade is considered too short to be classified as a sword, and yet at the same time it is too long to be a dagger. Consisting of a curved, single-edged blade, the Kodachi was wielded by Samurai during Japan's feudal period, and it may also have been used by civilians, who were not permitted to own longer swords such as those used by warriors and officials.

name: Sai
desciption: The sai's distinctive shape makes it a versatile weapon. With skill, it can be used effectively against a long sword by trapping the sword's blade between the sai's blade and the tsuba and breaking it with a twist of the hand.

name: Ninja Star
desciption: A lethal throwing weapon that can pierce an opponent's body before they realize an attack is under way. Conceal them, and then throw them underhand at an enemy when they least expect it.

name: Type 98 Anti Tank
desciption: Developed by the Chinese in the late ’90s, the Type 98 Anti-Tank is capable of firing unguided, high-explosive 120mm projectiles over a distance of nearly 2km. The weapon can be fired from the shoulder with minimal recoil and has been nicknamed the “Queen Bee” by its proponents.

name: Bushmaster Carbon 15
desciption: This top of the line assault weapon weighs less than three and a half pounds. A very effective weapon, regardless of the user's stats.

name: HEG
desciption: A high-explosive grenade used to cause casualties up to a maximum of 190 meters from the point of burst.

name: Taurus
desciption: This firearm has been engineered for reliability, accuracy and durability. One of the best low priced weapons you can buy.

name: Blowgun
desciption: Most often used with poison darts, can be quite effective if you don't wish your target to know they are under attack until it's far too late.

name: Bo Staff
desciption: A long stick carried in the hand. Can't take too much chopping, but its smooth reversal ability makes it a fluid and versatile weapon when used with skill.

name: Fireworks
desciption: A fascinating mix of charcoal, sulphur and saltpetre compressed into a bamboo tube. Traditionally fireworks are the sign of getting rid of the old and welcoming the new. When this is ignited and thrown at an opponent they will get a nasty surprise!

name: Katana
desciption: Curved, single-edged sword, or dao, traditionally used by the Japanese samurai. In well trained hands, a deadly weapon.

name: Qsz-92
desciption: Most recent development of the Chinese state arms factories. Dual stack magazine holds 15 rounds. Front part of the frame under the barrel is shaped as an accessory rail to accept laser sights or flash lights.

name: SKS Carbine
desciption: This gun, with the proper cartridges, will serve for deer hunting, pest and predator control, and emergency self defense.

name: Twin Tiger Hooks
desciption: This versatile and lethal weapon combines the abilities of a sword, cane and dagger. Perfect for trapping, blocking and slashing.

name: Wushu Double Axes
desciption: This is a pair of lethal axes first forged by the legendary Wushu Warrior Li Kwei. Designed to launch a flurry attack at the enemy, hacking and slashing them to pieces.

name: Ithaca 37
desciption: One of the oldest pump action shotguns still in production, this is a favourite of several generations.

name: Lorcin 380
desciption: This is the handgun most frequently submitted by law enforcement agencies for tracing in connection to violent crimes. Very low quality, so very much a "use and discard" weapon for short-range attacks.

name: S&W M29
desciption: A six shot double action revolver chambered for the .44 Magnum cartridge. It will also chamber and fire .44 Special cartridges.

name: Flamethrower
desciption: Built like a backpack, with dual tanks to hold the highly flammable gas. Be careful though, a well placed bullet could be the end of this powerful weapon.. and the person carrying it.

name: Tear Gas
desciption: Typically used for riot control, this non-lethal gas will temporarily blind your opponent, possibly giving you a bit of an advantage in battle.

name: Throwing Knife
desciption: To make the best use of this weapon, skill and practice are needed, but in the right hands, this could be used for a devastating attack.

name: Jaguar Plushie
desciption: Modelled after the third largest cat in the world, this small spotted plushie could be easily confused for a leopard.

name: Mayan Statue
desciption: Small, dark jade statue of the Mayan God Quetzalcoatl. Quetzalcoatl is the god of human sustenance, penitence, self-sacrifice, re-birth and butterflies.

name: Dahlia
desciption: Spectacular pink bloom with pointed petals, this is the national flower of Mexico.

name: Wolverine Plushie
desciption: The wolverine has been described as the fiercest creature on earth, but this small plush version will only growl if you pull its tail.

name: Hockey Stick
desciption: Replica of the sticks used in the 1920 Olympics, the first year Hockey was recognized as an official Olympic sport. The Winnipeg Falcons had the honour of taking the Gold medal home to Canada.

name: Crocus
desciption: This bright blue flower is often considered the national flower of Canada.

name: Orchid
desciption: Delicate pink flower, the orchid may not be a native of Hawaii, but it has made the transition to this tropical climate with ease.

name: Pele Charm
desciption: This Pele Charm is a miniature testament to the goddess's power and grandeur. Crafted from lustrous gold, this small talisman captures the fiery spirit of Pele, Hawaiian Goddess of Fire and Volcanoes. Its intricate detailing and radiant shine serve as a constant reminder of Pele's passionate nature and formidable strength. A possession as enchanting as it is empowering, the charm invites the wielder to embrace their own inner fervor and resilience.

name: Nessie Plushie
desciption: Hidden in the depths of the Loch. Seeing this mythical creature will leave a lasting impression.

name: Heather
desciption: Believed to bring good luck to who possess it. These spiky purple and white flowers cover the hillsides of Scotland.

name: Red Fox Plushie
desciption: Small dark red fox plushie, will serve as a memento from your trip to Britain, and your participation in a local Fox Hunt.

name: Monkey Plushie
desciption: Small plush monkey, made in the image of the simians, often seen around the forests of Argentina.

name: Soccer Ball
desciption: Named the Telstar, this iconic football was the official inflatable orb of the 1970 World Cup in Mexico. Consisting of 12 black pentagons and 20 white hexagons, the Telstar was designed to be more visible during black and white television broadcasts, even though hot pink and glitter would've stood out more. Nobody is quite sure why this football is so popular in Argentina, especially as 1970 was the only year they failed to qualify for the World Cup. One theory posits that the ball is often deflated and used as a makeshift toilet to disrespect the tournament's eventual winner and Argentina's hated neighbour, Brazil.

name: Ceibo Flower
desciption: This unusual red flower is the national flower of Argentina.

name: Edelweiss
desciption: Small white blooms are the hallmark of this Swiss national flower.

name: Chamois Plushie
desciption: Small plushie of a Mountain Goat.

name: Panda Plushie
desciption: One of the most recognizable endangered species, Xiong Mao, as they are called in Chinese, instantly bring to mind bamboo forests and quiet contemplation.

name: Jade Buddha
desciption: In a controversy the instant we feel anger we have already ceased striving for the truth, and have begun striving for ourselves. - Buddha

name: Peony
desciption: While China has no official national flower, the peony, with its ruffled, pale pink blooms, is widely recognized as the national favourite.

name: Cherry Blossom
desciption: This beautiful pink blossom is often considered the official flower of Japan.

name: Kabuki Mask
desciption: Used in traditional Japanese theater productions, this beautiful mask can serve as a reminder of your recent trip to Tokyo.

name: Maneki Neko
desciption: Meant to bring good fortune and prosperity to its owner, this little cat is more than just a good luck charm.

name: Elephant Statue
desciption: This ancient ivory statue is made from the tusks of the very animal it represents,and harvesting the tusks for such artworks is ironically bringing the elephant to the brink of extinction.

name: Lion Plushie
desciption: This small plushie is modelled after the African lion. Squeeze his tummy to hear him roar.

name: African Violet
desciption: While not the national flower for Africa, this beautiful purple plant will remind you of your recent trip to the Southern African plains.

name: Donator Pack
desciption: A Torn City donator pack. Using this will credit you with 31 donator days and give you 60 points!

name: Bronze Paint Brush
desciption: This item was given for third place in one of the many art competitions held by Torn City Staff.

name: Silver Paint Brush
desciption: This item was given for second place in one of the many art competitions held by Torn City Staff.

name: Gold Paint Brush
desciption: This item was given for first place in one of the many art competitions held by Torn City Staff.

name: Pand0ra's Box
desciption: After being hidden for years this ancient relic has resurfaced. Mysterious wonders or tragic events await the owner. Open the box if you dare--but following your curiosity may take you down unexpected paths.

name: Mr Brownstone Doll
desciption: This rocked out doll will get up around seven Get outta bed around nine And dont worry about nothing 'cause worryin is a waste of ...time.

name: Dual Axes
desciption: Only a well trained individual would even dare to attempt to dual wield these weapons.

name: Dual Hammers
desciption: Only a well trained individual, ideally with some experience in carpentry, would even dare to attempt to dual wield these weapons.

name: Dual Scimitars
desciption: Only a well trained individual would even dare to attempt to dual wield these weapons, and even then only after several puffs on a hookah.

name: Dual Samurai Swords
desciption: Only a well trained individual, wearing a classy kimono, would even dare to attempt to dual wield these weapons.

name: Japanese/English Dictionary
desciption: This Dictionary can aid you in translating words and symbols from Japanese to English or vice-versa.

name: Bottle of Sake
desciption: Sake, an alcoholic beverage of Japanese origin, is created through the fermentation and brewing of rice. In its homeland, the consumption of sake involves a ritual process where the drink is warmed in a small bottle before being served in an even smaller porcelain cup. Such customs are rarely practiced in Torn, where sake is most commonly served from a tramp's shoe and drunk in a bathroom stall prior to a crime spree.

name: Oriental Log
desciption: This piece of Japanese oak looks ancient. It has Japanese symbols carved all over it. Strangely, written in English on the bottom of the log there is the name 'Master Keneshi'.

name: Oriental Log Translation
desciption: On a piece of paper is written: He who chooses to undertake the mastery of dual weaponry need only speak my name.

name: YouYou Yo Yo
desciption: You can walk the dog, rock the cradle but be careful, this YouYou YoYo could turn you into meme!

name: Monkey Cuffs
desciption: These shiny steel manacles are used by MoNKeY to capture and restrain the bad guys of Torn City. Some lucky ladies hint they have a more naughty purpose!

name: Jester's Cap
desciption: A constant reminder that you should never take things too seriously. Wearing this cap will allow you to act a fool and be praised for it.

name: Gibal's Dragonfly
desciption: Gibal rides around Torn City on her dragonfly looking for wrong-doers. Once caught they are locked up for good!

name: Green Ornament
desciption: This ornament was given to Officers of Torn City for Xmas in recognition of a job well done for their time served as staff.

name: Purple Ornament
desciption: This ornament was given to Helpers of Torn City for Xmas in recognition of a job well done for their time served as staff.

name: Blue Ornament
desciption: This ornament was given to Mods of Torn City for Xmas in recognition of a job well done for their time served as staff.

name: Purple Bell
desciption: This ornament was given to Admins of Torn City for Xmas in recognition of a job well done for their time served as staff.

name: Mistletoe
desciption: A kiss under the mistletoe is said to bring good luck for the year ahead. Why not share this tradition with someone special this year?

name: Mini Sleigh
desciption: A miniature replica of the very same one Santa uses when delivering presents to the good boys and girls of Torn City.

name: Snowman
desciption: Comes complete with silk top hat, carrot nose, and two eyes made out of coal. Perfect winter decoration for any home.

name: Christmas Gnome
desciption: A small misshapen mischievous sprite who makes Christmas wishes of 2006 come true.

name: Gingerbread House
desciption: Snowdrifts of icing, walls of gingerbread: this house is a replica of the first home decorated for Xmas in Torn City.

name: Lollipop
desciption: Tasty fruity candy lolly for lovers, friends, whiny noobs and spoilt brats alike to enjoy! Available in strawberry, blueberry, banana and chocolate flavours. Provides a small happiness increase when consumed.

name: Mardi Gras Beads
desciption: These beads are from the Mardi Gras and thrown by Body. Do you have what it takes to get a set of them?

name: Devil Toy
desciption: Tasmanian devil that is. This little fella has been known to create havoc wherever he goes including staff channels, faction forums and anywhere newbies lurk. Rumour has it only Tazzy can control this little whirlwind.

name: Cookie Launcher
desciption: A non-working replica of Mix's Cookie launcher, used to launch cookies at his IRC buddies.

name: Cursed Moon Pendant
desciption: Be wary of this sacred item. The bearer of this pendant will be put under a spell and become a slave to the evillest of all staff members, Luna. The maker of this pendant cannot be held responsible for any actions you may perform while under its spell. You have been warned.

name: Apartment Blueprint
desciption: Designs of an Apartment for construction purposes.

name: Semi-Detached House Blueprint
desciption: Designs of a Semi-Detached house for construction purposes.

name: Detached House Blueprint
desciption: Designs of a Detached house for construction purposes.

name: Beach House Blueprint
desciption: Designs of a Beach house for construction purposes.

name: Chalet Blueprint
desciption: Designs of a Chalet for construction purposes.

name: Villa Blueprint
desciption: Designs of a Villa for construction purposes.

name: Penthouse Blueprint
desciption: Designs of a Penthouse for construction purposes.

name: Mansion Blueprint
desciption: Designs of a Mansion for construction purposes.

name: Ranch Blueprint
desciption: Designs of a Ranch for construction purposes.

name: Palace Blueprint
desciption: Designs of a Palace for construction purposes.

name: Castle Blueprint
desciption: Designs of a Castle for construction purposes.

name: Printing Paper
desciption: Paper, very similar to the type money is printed on.

name: Blank Tokens
desciption: Blank casino token slugs.

name: PVC Cards
desciption: A stack of high-quality Polyvinyl Chloride (PVC) cards, each with a printable surface ready to be customized to your needs. Whether you're looking to forge a driver's license or create a membership card for The Torn City Society of Fieldmice, this durable and flexible material will ensure that your design looks authentic even if you've just printed it off at home!

name: Skateboard
desciption: Device used for transportation and entertainment.

name: Boxing Gloves
desciption: Worn to protect hands during a boxing event.

name: Dumbbells
desciption: Device used to increase muscle mass.

name: Combat Vest
desciption: This prototype armor improves on the build of the Outer Tactical Vest to bring its wearer even more protection, making it the lightest, most technologically advanced piece of protective armor ever issued to the Armed Forces of the United States.

name: Liquid Body Armor
desciption: Liquid polyethylene glycol and hard nano-particles of silica combined and soaked into all layers of kevlar to make a uniquely flexible and lightweight body armor with amazing stopping power. Top Secret development model!

name: Flexible Body Armor
desciption: Classified! Top Secret!

name: Stick of Dynamite
desciption: A small stick of dynamite. This thing could cause a lot of damage if used in the right place...

name: Cesium-137
desciption: A man made radioactive element produced by breaking up uranium atoms. It remains dangerous for hundreds of years until losing its radiation.

name: Dirty Bomb
desciption: A weapon which combines radioactive material with explosives. A dirty bomb would be unlikely to cause many deaths; its main purpose would be to cause a mass panic.

name: Sh0rty's Surfboard
desciption: Feel the force of Sh0rty's surfboard as he rides past you working his way around Torn City!

name: Puzzle Piece
desciption: This oddly shaped item was left over from the last time its owner, Chris, attempted to do a puzzle. Holds some importance....

name: Hunny Pot
desciption: This Hunny pot is gold plated and is filled with all the yummy sweetness of honey from contented bees. It is believed to contain the source of Acid's sweetness.

name: Seductive Stethoscope
desciption: The enigmatic Drmark uses this cold instrument to pick up the heated flutter of a lovestruck lady or the palpitations of a troubled wrongdoer, keeping the population of Torn City healthy.

name: Dollar Bill Collectible
desciption: This item is so rare that only a few bills were printed. It can only be obtained on the item market during Dollar Day Sales. It costs one dollar to purchase, but due to limited printing it is worth a small fortune.

name: Backstage Pass
desciption: This backstage pass gave special benefits to its holder by allowing them to have met performers after concerts held by Torn City Radio.

name: Chemi's Magic Potion
desciption: This homemade pink brew is powerful, one sip will leave you feeling like you can beat anyone.

name: Pack of Trojans
desciption: Magnum rubbers for the gangster who really knows how to use his gun.

name: Pair of High Heels
desciption: High Heels - essential weaponry in the control of the male species. Ho or Foe, still can be used to smack an average Joe.

name: Thong
desciption: Thongs...Not a wise choice if you have too much junk in your trunk.

name: Hazmat Suit
desciption: A fully encapsulating garment worn as protection from hazardous materials or substances.

name: Flea Collar
desciption: Keep those pesky critters away whilst swinging round the city. A rare must-have before it was discontinued. Reminiscent of golden times. The tag reads "Shadow Still a pup".

name: Dunkin's Donut
desciption: The feeling of invincibility gained by eating one of these cream filled masterpieces has been known to make HOF factions tremble with fear.

name: Amazon Doll
desciption: Modeled after Wild_Irish_Btch, this doll shows that women can stomp your face into the ground while towering above the men of Torn City. Doll comes equipped with a bag of Cheetos, a Teddy Bear plushie, a replica of Brutus, and an avid love of midgets.

name: BBQ Smoker
desciption: You have to be pretty fast to steal the brisket inside this smoker. Which just happened to be stolen right after this collectible was made. Body and a drifter hobo were both seen eating brisket in the vicinity shortly afterwards. st0ne was last seen crying in his backyard.

name: Bag of Cheetos
desciption: A jumbo bag of these orange cheese twists for late nights on the job. Favored by midgets of all types.

name: Motorbike
desciption: You can often find Numbat tearing it up through the city's darkest streets on this, seeking prey. Beware the spiked tires!

name: Citrus Squeezer

name: Leopard Coin
desciption: An attempt by Edward III to produce a gold coin to be used internationally, much like the Florin but only half of the value. The Leopard bore the following Latin legend: 'DOMINE NE IN FURORE TUO ARGUAS ME', meaning: 'O Lord, rebuke me not in Thy anger'. The Florin was recalled and melted down in 1344 to produce the Noble. Few specimens have survived of what is often regarded as one of the most beautiful medieval coins ever produced.

name: Florin Coin
desciption: An English coin based on a French coin, and issued in Florence, Italy in 1252. The Florin was made from gold and was intended as an international coin, however the gold it was made from was overvalued and the coin was not accepted by international merchants. The coin was then withdrawn from circulation and melted down to form the Noble. Because of this, the Florin is very rare.

name: Gold Noble Coin
desciption: The first mass-produced English coin, preceded by the Florin, the gold Noble was valued at six shillings and eight pence. The coin was introduced in 1344, and weighed 138.5 grains, later reduced to 128.5 grains. Mentioned in Shakespeare's plays, this coin is sought after by museums and private collectors.

name: Ganesha Sculpture
desciption: Also known as Ganapati, worshipped widely throughout Hindu India as the remover of obstacles. Ganesha has figured often in Indian art since around 100 AD. This rare work is made from gold and is highly sought after as part of a set of South Asian artifacts.

name: Vairocana Buddha Sculpture
desciption: The Vairocana Buddha is an embodiment of Dharmakaya. It is well known as the generalised depiction of the historical Gautama Buddha.Throughout Asia the image has different meanings: in Tibet - 'the illuminator' and in Japan - 'great sun'. Not as common as other Buddhist sculptures, this valuable gold specimen is a great collector's item.

name: Quran Script : Ibn Masud
desciption: The Qur'an, which in Arabic means 'the recitation', is recognized by Muslims as the main miracle of prophet Muhammad, and is a compilation of divine messages. It is a book of guidance as opposed to an account of specific events. This particular script is the Ibn Masud version, and is extremely valuable in a set of all three versions.

name: Quran Script : Ubay Ibn Ka'b
desciption: The Qur'an, which in Arabic means 'the recitation', is recognized by Muslims as the main miracle of prophet Muhammad, and is a compilation of divine messages. It is a book of guidance as opposed to an account of specific events. This particular script is the Ubay Ibn Ka'b version, and is extremely valuable in a set of all three versions.

name: Quran Script : Ali
desciption: The Qur'an, which in Arabic means 'the recitation', is recognized by Muslims as the main miracle of prophet Muhammad, and is a compilation of divine messages. It is a book of guidance as opposed to an account of specific events. This particular script is the Ali version, and is extremely valuable in a set of all three versions.

name: Shabti Sculpture
desciption: Shabtis were placed in the tomb among the gods of the grave, acting as a substitute for the dead. The Egyptians believed that when they passed into the afterlife they would be called to do manual labour. The shabtis would then take their place and do the work, leaving the deceased to rest in peace. Shabtis from famous tombs are very rare, reflecting their high value.

name: Egyptian Amulet
desciption: These amulets, often in the form of a scarab beetle, were left in tombs as grave goods or given to people and the gods as presents. The Scarab, or 'Kheper' (which means "to transform"), was used in many of the pharaonic names. Pharaoh Amenhotep III was famous for his group of '5 scarabs'. This particular amulet is made from fired clay.

name: White Senet Pawn
desciption: An ancient game piece used in the game of Senet. As a complete set of 5 white pawns, 5 black pawns, and the Senet board, this collection would be very valuable to any collector or museum.

name: Black Senet Pawn
desciption: An ancient game piece used in the game of Senet. As a complete set of 5 white pawns, 5 black pawns, and the Senet board, this collection would be very valuable to any collector or museum.

name: Senet Board
desciption: Senet, or Senat is regarded as possibly the oldest board game in the world. Found in Predynastic and First Dynasty burials of Egypt, around 3500BC and 3100BC. The game is similar to draughts, with a board of 30 squares (3x10). The game is played with two sets of at least 5 pawns. Although Senet sets are mass produced today, this original set from around 3200BC would be priceless for a keen collector.

name: Epinephrine
desciption: Epinephrine is released from the adrenal glands when the user is in danger or excited. It prepares the user for these situations by boosting the supply of oxygen and glucose to the brain and muscles also increasing heart rate and suppressing the immune system. When used in combat, this steroid will provide a massive bonus to strength.

name: Melatonin
desciption: Melatonin reduces the effects of disease and pain and in other tests, Melatonin can possibly increase one's concentration levels. When used in combat, this steroid will provide a massive bonus to speed.

name: Serotonin
desciption: Serotonin acts as a pain killer, and helps with blood clotting. Tests on animals show that serotonin can make the animal more dominant and aggressive. When used in combat, this steroid will provide a massive bonus to defense, and may even replenish some life.

name: Snow Globe '09
desciption: These sit quietly all year round out of view, but at Christmas time one shake of this globe is the perfect reminder of the festive season.

name: Dancing Santa Claus '09
desciption: This hand me down from your favourite auntie lights up the room and gets everyone singing their favourite Christmas carols.

name: Christmas Stocking '09
desciption: This stocking is never worn, but at Christmas time it is filled with lots of tasty goodies and hopefully a few presents.

name: Santa's Elf '09
desciption: Santa's elves work hard all year round. This figurine was made in recognition of their efforts, and is sold in secret stores around the city.

name: Christmas Card '09
desciption: Send this clever card, made from 100% recycled paper, to your loved ones at Christmas. It has a sweet festive rhyme inside if you are lost for words.

name: Admin Portrait '09
desciption: A portrait of Clansy, Wolfeh, Davz and Ched. To hang above the mantel while the fire glows. We give you this gift because we care, No really we dont mind if you sit and stare. We know you guys luff us the best, Ched even wore his best Christmas vest. Merry Christmas!

name: Blue Easter Egg
desciption: Fear not, mortal. You are now under the protection of Blue. Guarded by my presence, danger itself shall fear you. Your human form is frail and weak. But with my help, thou art fortified against all peril. Together, we shall defy death. I will see to it that you resist the lure of the afterlife with every ounce of strength. Onward, soldier. To victory!

name: Green Easter Egg
desciption: Hey champ! Are you ready to take on the world? No worries if not. But if you are in the right place spiritually, I'm here for you with a bolt of fresh, organic, unfiltered, recycled, cruelty-free filtered energy. Gulp me down and feel me deep inside your core! Because with my green glow on your side, you'll be ready to attack the day and crush your goals. I believe in you. Carpe diem!

name: Red Easter Egg
desciption: Lookin' for a lil nerve, are ya? Thought so. Folks always come crawling back to old red when they're feelin' yellow. That happy little freak might make ya'll giddy inside, but old red will kick you in the balls and pull you up by your bootstraps. And then steal your boots. And kick you in the balls again. What was I sayin? Ah, who gives a rat's hole. Wanna burn a warehouse?

name: Yellow Easter Egg
desciption: Isn't Torn City great? Life is good here. All the people are so friendly and kind. Look at that cute squirrel! I wonder if he has a family. Families are great. I love to think about my family and smile. Do you like smiling? Smile with me. Let's smile together. Oh wow, there's that squirrel again. Is he smiling? I had no idea squirrels could smile. A smile is the best thing to wear, and it's free! What are you wearing? A frown? Let's turn that frown... You guessed it! Upside down. Hahaha. We're having so much fun together.

name: White Easter Egg
desciption: Welcome to the circle of sobriety, friend. There are no judgments here, only love. By embracing my light, you will take the first step on the long road to recovery. My white exterior represents hope. Hope that you will one day free yourself from the chains of addiction. Each time you partake of my pureness, the grip of substance shall release a little more. Give me your hand. Let us form a circle. One egg at a time, we will conquer your demons together.

name: Black Easter Egg
desciption: Money makes the world go round, and the black egg is here to make sure you're spinning in the right direction. My returns are uncorrelated with traditional asset classes, providing valuable diversification in the field of portfolio optimization. Your eyes have glazed over. Don't worry, I've got this. You want to be a high roller, right? First, you have to roll the dough. Then, we make bread.

name: Gold Easter Egg
desciption: Feeling tired, bro? No sweat, bro. The gold egg's got your back. I'll have you powering through your fitness goals in less time than it takes to make scrambles. We're gonna crush it, broseph. Unless you wanna be a field mouse for the rest of your life. Is that what you want? Huh? Answer me. What's up, cat got your tongue, wickle mousey? There we go. Now you're getting pissed off. I like that. Use it. Abuse it. Unleash the beast within!

name: Metal Dog Tag
desciption: A solid metal dog tag, given to winners of the yearly happy tagging competition.

name: Bronze Dog Tag
desciption: A solid bronze dog tag, given to the 3rd place winner of the yearly happy tagging competition.

name: Silver Dog Tag
desciption: A solid silver dog tag, given to the 2nd place winner of the yearly happy tagging competition.

name: Gold Dog Tag
desciption: A solid gold dog tag, given to the 1st place winner of the yearly happy tagging competition.

name: MP5k
desciption: A short version of the standard MP5. The MP5k is a short-range weapon with a lot of fire power.

name: AK74U
desciption: A shortened AK74. The AK74U has roughly the same dimensions and range as most Submachine Guns, but has the advantage of standard issue assault rifle ammunition.

name: Skorpion
desciption: This Czech weapon was designed for police, but is also used by some military units. It offers single shot, 3 burst fires and fully automatic functions.

name: TMP
desciption: This modern SMG has a blowback operated, locked breech design. The TMP has no stock and can therefore, only be fired from pistol-style.

name: Thompson
desciption: An American blowback SMG. The Thompson takes a double row, box magazine designed to be inserted from below.

name: MP 40
desciption: Made in Germany, the MP40 is an open bolt, blowback operated Submachine Gun. Has a slow rate of fire and little recoil, and is useful for single shots rather than bursts.

name: Luger
desciption: Also known as the "Parabellum Pistole". This name comes from the Latin phrase "Si vis pacem, para bellum"--"if you want peace, prepare for war." A semi-automatic 9mm handgun.

name: Blunderbuss
desciption: The Blunderbuss is a muzzle loading, single shot, short barrelled firearm. It is an early form of shotgun adapted to be used for personal and military defense.

name: Zombie Brain
desciption: A zombie brain, carefully dissected from the head of a zombie.

name: Human Head
desciption: A trophy for some zombies. A tasty snack for others.

name: Medal of Honor
desciption: Given to the valiant troops who lead their flag to victory in the World War competition.

name: Limoen Saxon
desciption: The Limoen Saxon is mightily quick off the line, and actually has the joint-best acceleration rating of any Class E car along with the Çagoutte 10-6. However, its small, 1,400cc engine means it will struggle in a straight line fight, and you'd be advised to abandon this vehicle the minute you enter Class D.

name: Nano Pioneer
desciption: Nano drivers tend to fall into one of two categories. Either they're lifelong fans of this classic British brand, or they're too cheap to pay for gas. If you ever see the Nano Pioneer overtake you on the track you're in trouble, as this is one of the slowest cars available in Torn City. But that's actually a bonus in some ways, as the Nano's 8 inch braking discs couldn't stop a snail if it were mooching.

name: Vita Bravo
desciption: The Vita Bravo is a solid investment for Class E drivers as despite its relatively poor top end speed it remains competitive when pitted against Class D vehicles. And despite its low dirt rating, this car seems to do well on full or partial mud tracks, where the Bravo's superior handling often wins out.

name: Zaibatsu Macro
desciption: Most people only ever find themselves in the seat of a Zaibatsu Macro when they're taking their driving test, and with good reason. The Macro handling is abysmal, and this would be dangerous if it could ever reach anything beyond a mid-range top speed. That being said, the braking on these vehicles is absolutely first class, which is probably a good thing if you've got a GTA-addicted teenager in the driving seat.

name: Çagoutte 10-6
desciption: This French hot hatch is popular in its class due to its rapid acceleration, and unlike the Limoen Saxon, this car has the pace to make use of it. If you're looking to purchase a Çagoutte 10-6, your best bet is to try the nearest wreck yard, or perhaps a large tree on a shaded corner, since this car's brakes appear to be made of cotton candy.

name: Papani Colé
desciption: Papani's Colé model is a great choice for Class E drivers who need pace over precision. This car's 16-valve engine may have little torque, but once it hits top speed you'll find others in its class will struggle to catch up, especially if you're down at the Docks or barrelling around the Speedway.

name: Bedford Racer
desciption: A favorite among everyone's girlfriend during the early 2000's, the Bedford Racer is a safe little motor whose brakes are far and away its most impressive asset. Unfortunately, you'll rarely get a chance to test them, since this is one of the slowest cars in Class E, or in any class, for that matter.

name: Stålhög 860
desciption: Stålhög's USP lies in the sturdiness and strength of their cars. The 860 is no different, with this battleship weighing in at a colossal two tonnes. But while this model's braking may leave much to be desired, the Stålhög 860 is among the fastest of its class, and can easily exceed 100mph on the straights.

name: Alpha Milano 156
desciption: Alpha Milano's 156 model possesses a large amount of torque, giving it great acceleration off the line. The tradeoff comes in the braking department, with this being one of a number of areas where this car suffers from reliability issues.

name: Bavaria X5
desciption: Handling is not the X5's strong point, with one online review describing it as "sharp as a tug boat on tarmac." Nevertheless, the X5's superior braking makes it more than capable of setting Class D records across both dirt and tarmac.

name: Coche Basurero
desciption: The Coche Basurero is something of a joke in Torn, since you're far more likely to see it at the dump than on the road. Nevertheless, this turbo charged European hatchback remains a useful Class D vehicle, with its poor top speed compensated for by superb acceleration off the line.

name: Bedford Nova
desciption: With a top speed of 150mph the Bedford Nova is the fastest in its class by some margin. Unfortunately, it'll take you some time to get there since the Nova's dreaded torque steer means all its power is put through the front wheels, giving it some of the poorest acceleration stats of any D class vehicle.

name: Verpestung Sport
desciption: Either of the Verpestungs available in Torn will serve you well in a D-class dirt race, but as its name suggests, the Sport is slightly quicker than the Insecta, albeit by a paltry 2mph. When it comes to the tarmac, Torn's racers find that this king of the hot hatches is often beaten by the Insecta at all but a handful of tracks.

name: Echo S3
desciption: The Echo S3 is considered an elite car among Class C vehicles, with their limited top speed compensated for by strong acceleration. These models are often given out as runner-up prizes via the URT, and their rarity means they can change hands for several billion dollars due to their collectible status.

name: Volt RS
desciption: The Volt RS's top speed of 163mph makes it only the third-fastest in Class C, but where it stands alone is the rapid acceleration provided by its 300bhp, 2.5 liter turbocharged engine.
